'''
Kata: https://www.codewars.com/kata/535474308bb336c9980006f2
My profile: https://www.codewars.com/users/Thundiverter
Language: Python

Description:
Write a method that takes one argument as name and then greets that name, capitalized and ends with an exclamation point.

Example:

<code>"riley" --> "Hello Riley!"
"JACK"  --> "Hello Jack!"</code>
'''

# Solution #1
def greet(name):
    return 'Hello ' + name.capitalize() + '!'

# Solution #2
def greet(name): 
    return 'Hello {name}!'.format(name=name.capitalize())
